{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 4.1.4 Open Scholarship ecosystem\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Four major elements exist as preconditions to Open Scholarship adoption:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab USERS: Awareness of Open Scholarship to engage with the practices.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab PROCESS: Open Scholarship tools that guide adoption of practices.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab CONTEXT: Community and systemic support to create a sustainable Open Scholarship environment.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab INCENTIVES: Motivations to engage with the practices.\sa180\par}
